  "body": "<h3 style=\"text-align: left;margin: 0px;font-size: 20px;padding-bottom: 0px;padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom:10px;padding-left: 0px;padding-right: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, Verdana, Trebuchet MS; color: #222;\">In their own words</h3>\n<p style=\"padding: 0px 0px 20px 0px;line-height: 24px;margin: 0px;text-align: left; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, Verdana, Trebuchet MS; margin: 0px;\">There are many personal reasons people collect fine art. It can be as\nsimple as enjoying the beauty of a unique painting, as it becomes the focal\npoint within your special room. Often the painting speaks to you on a deep\npersonal level, that only you can describe. One of our customers and a\ngood friend, Bennet L., recently put it this way: \"The joy one derives from\nowning art, especially when the art reflects or represents something in their\nlife is a joy forevever.... Every painting that I own has its own unique story\nand memory. Some go back to childhood, some are in its acquisition,\nsome are centered on location, but all either individually or collectively are\na treasure and a memory.\"</p>\n\n<table width=\"100%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td width=\"48%\" align=\"center\" valign=\"middle\"><a href=\"https://www.bedfordfineartgallery.com/daniel_charles_grose_lillies.html\"><img style=\"width: 85%; height:auto;\" src=\"https://www.bedfordfineartgallery.com/mailers/img/grose.jpg\" width=\"575\" height=\"377\" alt=\"Daniel Charles Grose (American 1838 – 1900)\n\"></a></td>\n      <td width=\"48%\" align=\"center\" valign=\"middle\"><a href=\"https://www.bedfordfineartgallery.com/james_l_adams_boulders.html\"><img style=\"width: 85%; height:auto;\" src=\"https://www.bedfordfineartgallery.com/mailers/img/adams_grid.jpg\" width=\"643\" height=\"419\" alt=\"James L Adams (British 1847-1901)\n\"></a></td>\n   \n    </tr>\n    <tr><td colspan=\"3\"><div style=\"padding-top: 10px;\">&nbsp;</div></td></tr>\n    <tr>\n       <td width=\"48%\" align=\"center\" valign=\"middle\"><a href=\"https://www.bedfordfineartgallery.com/earl_lincoln_poole_titmouse.html\"><img style=\"width: 54%; height:auto;\" src=\"https://www.bedfordfineartgallery.com/mailers/img/earl_lincoln_poole_grid.jpg\" width=\"281\" height=\"426\" alt=\"Earl Lincoln Poole (American 1891 – 1972) \n\"></a></td>\n      <td width=\"48%\" align=\"center\" valign=\"middle\"><a href=\"https://www.bedfordfineartgallery.com/frederick_stone_batcheller_flowers.html\"><img style=\"width: 54%; height:auto;\" src=\"https://www.bedfordfineartgallery.com/mailers/img/batch_grid.jpg\" width=\"312\" height=\"474\" alt=\"Frederick Stone Batcheller (American 1837-1889)\n\"></a></td>\n\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;margin: 0px;font-size: 20px;padding-bottom: 0px;padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom:10px;padding-left: 0px;padding-right: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, Verdana, Trebuchet MS; color: #222; border-top: 1px solid #f2f2f2; margin-top: 40px;\">American Values</h3>\n<p style=\"padding: 0px 0px 20px 0px;line-height: 24px;margin: 0px;text-align: left; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, Verdana, Trebuchet MS; margin: 0px;\">\"The credit belongs to those who are actually in the arena, who strive\nvaliantly; who know the great enthusiasms, the great devotions, and spend\nthemselves in a worthy cause; who at best know the triumph of high\nachievement; and who, at worst, if they fail, fail while daring greatly, so that\ntheir place shall never be with those cold and timid souls who know neither\nvictory nor defeat.\"<br> – Theodore Roosevelt</p>\n<table width=\"100%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td width=\"30%\" align=\"center\" valign=\"middle\"><a href=\"https://www.bedfordfineartgallery.com/william_samuel_horton_roosevelt.html\"><img style=\"width: 96%; height:auto;\" src=\"https://www.bedfordfineartgallery.com/mailers/img/horton.jpg\" width=\"258\" height=\"312\" alt=\"William Samuel Horton (American 1865 – 1936)\n\"></a></td>\n      <td width=\"30%\" align=\"center\" valign=\"middle\"><a href=\"https://www.bedfordfineartgallery.com/george_washington_chromolithograph.html\"><img style=\"width: 80%; height:auto;\" src=\"https://www.bedfordfineartgallery.com/mailers/img/wash.jpg\" width=\"241\" height=\"346\" alt=\"George Washington chromolithograph, American 19th century\n\"></a></td>\n      <td width=\"30%\" align=\"center\" valign=\"middle\"><a href=\"https://www.bedfordfineartgallery.com/c_myron_clark_constitution.html\"><img style=\"width: 94%; height:auto;\" src=\"https://www.bedfordfineartgallery.com/mailers/img/c_myron_clark_grid.jpg\" width=\"294\" height=\"368\" alt=\"C. Myron Clark (American 1858 – 1925) \n\"></a></td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr><td colspan=\"3\"><div style=\"padding-top: 10px;\">&nbsp;</div></td></tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td width=\"30%\" align=\"center\" valign=\"middle\"><a href=\"https://www.bedfordfineartgallery.com/clarence_drew_bartlett_franklin.html\"><img style=\"width: 94%; height:auto;\" src=\"https://www.bedfordfineartgallery.com/mailers/img/bartlett.jpg\" width=\"289\" height=\"340\" alt=\"Clarence Drew Bartlett (American, born 1863)\n\"></a></td>\n      <td width=\"30%\" align=\"center\" valign=\"middle\"><a href=\"https://www.bedfordfineartgallery.com/gayle_b_tate_washington.html\"><img style=\"width: 94%; height:auto;\" src=\"https://www.bedfordfineartgallery.com/mailers/img/tate_grid.jpg\" width=\"389\" height=\"386\" alt=\"Gayle B. Tate (American 1944 - )\n\"></a></td>\n      <td width=\"30%\" align=\"center\" valign=\"middle\"><a href=\"https://www.bedfordfineartgallery.com/albert_francis_king_art_lincoln.html\"><img style=\"width: 94%; height:auto;\" src=\"https://www.bedfordfineartgallery.com/mailers/img/afk_grid4.jpg\" width=\"296\" height=\"370\" alt=\"Albert Francis King (American 1854 – 1945)\n\"></a></td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>"
